caption: Really creative menu in an even more creative space. Love the classic hip hop vibe. My favorite dishes were the quail, wagyu, and chowder - all were rich in flavor and texture. The waffle was probably the only dish that didn't really impress. Wait staff was fun and gave us a shot of mezcal to finish off the night. Overall a great tasting menu, definitely one that I would recommend.

Schwa is a very special place. Chef Michael Carlson is an incredible chef and a human being with a great heart. Everyone at Schwa are five star chefs and they are awesome. I took some friends and one of my sons for dinner and everyone loved it as much as I did.

One of my favorite healthy spots in the city. I’ve had almost everything on the menu and it’s all good. Went last night and everything was clean, well spaced, and the service was excellent. If you’re looking for covid friendly indoor dining …

Dined with my daughter. We so enjoyed the vibes, the music, the staff, ambience, etc. The food was AMAZING!!! our first course was the "Arnold Palmer". arrived on a tray of artificial turf with cubes of food on gold tees. Way fun and Way delicious. Each course was constructed, deconstructed, reconstructed: original and tasty beyond belief. we brought a bottle of whiskey for the kitchen and a bottle of white and red for us. The staff guided us on wine choice for each course. An entertaining evening. Can't wait to return. :)

This HAS to be THE hippest restaurant in the world with a Michelin star. From the time you arrive outside it's totally like visiting an extremely cool 'dive bar'. But from the moment they engage with you it's like....'wait a minute, these guys are serious gastronomes'.....9 course tasting menu is what you'll have and it's a fantastic array of tastes....perfectly timed, just the right portions, excellent 'flow'.....and one of the things I love (and miss) about Chicago is you bring your own wine/booze....there's corkage fee, but for me that's THE way to do it for real wine-lovers. Anyway, come here if you can.

Absolutely fantastic! Such a cool concept, even weird at some point, but  very laud music, cool server, fun times! Food was excellent. Not fancy, very chill and relaxing atmosphere. I'm very happy I had a chance to experience this type of dining.
Excellent take out menu! We had their 6 course menu last weekend and I was awesome. I thought it might not be enough food, but it filled us up and we raved about each course.
One of my favorite restaurants ever. Unassuming setting, not fancy or upscale in decor or service, but the best most creative food around. Set tasting menu,byob.

Awesome experience until the end when everyone got a shot and somehow we weren’t worthy! The food was delish but we like to drink and when the wet socks next to us got shots and we didn’t, it kind of sucked! We’ll go home and have our own anniversary shots, but be prepared to be left out when the shots come out!
Ate at Schwa about 2 years ago and was one of the most enjoyable dining experiences I have had. Went back recently for their DIY carry out and they delivered  again. Highly recommend both.

Incredible experience. Even with social distancing, this restaurant is churning out magic. Bring a bottle per person - make sure one is sparkling and avoid heavy reds. Something for the kitchen never hurts.
excellent spot to spend time alone or talk business. looking forward to a return trip. the place has a great feel to it.

Love the innovative dish that mix Asian element together with western elements.  Surprising taste and dish display.  Overall definitely worth trying,  although some courses are a little salty for me. The only complain(not true complain) is the music is a little too loud that sometimes the waiter need to yell hahaha.

I know this is a legacy restaurant in Chicago, and I wish nothing but the best for any Chicago restaurant these days... But when paying $160 per person for a tasting menu, I should not leave a restaurant hungry. The pita bread and pita filling were counted as two separate courses. More troubling, the 12 "course" (9 dish) menu included not one, but two separate sorbet courses? We had some dishes that were real winners, but the overall meal seemed rushed (entrance to check in under 90 minutes), unthoughtful, and odd. Not even close to worth the price, Chicago has MUCH better to offer.
For a one star Michelin restaurant, you wouldn't expect approximately 8 of the 12 courses to be desserts... But yet here we are. If you're looking for a Michelin restaurant, don't choose this one.
Always amazing and tonight did not disappoint! Staff was very cognizant of following COVID guidelines. Food was awesome!
Great as always. Innovative, risky,  elegant while fun and relaxed at the same time. 12 courses was rushed with the timing but with COVID, it's understandable. Everything was perfect, delicious.
The only Reason this is not 5 stars is the loud music. The mackerel was not my favorite, but everything else was Michelin 3 star worthy. My husband won't stop talking about the eel ice cream

I've eaten at a number of Michelin restaurants, but Schwa is the one that has the most inventive and playful food I've had. I really enjoyed the flow from the beginning where it was lighter courses, to the end where each dish became more and more complex.  Schwa is one of the best places I've eaten.
Incredible and unique experience! The food was so delicious and inventive and the service was great as well. It was well worth the money for a truly one of a kind meal.

We lucked into a 5 PM reservation on a Saturday night while visiting in Chicago. Do not miss this place. The food was obviously amazing, but I was surprised how much fun it was at the same time.  I didn’t know exactly what to expect, this being my first experience at a Michelin starred restaurant. However it felt completely comfortable and laid-back from the moment we entered and they asked my first name.  The service was excellent, with different people bringing out different dishes. I’m pretty sure the servers were also cooks. Seemed like everyone was involved with both the front and back of house experience, which is something I had not seen before. Every course we had was imaginative, tasty and most of all fun. Will be back next time we are in town for sure!
Loved the atmosphere. Loved the food!
Bold delicate flavors making this place a unique restaurant, A culinary Wonder
What the heck this place is incredible
Amazing food, served by the chefs
A flavorful foodie experience. Now you know.
I literally asked the person at the table next to me if I could lick their plate. The quail egg ravioli is definitely the best thing I have ever tasted. The staff is great, the food is even better.
(Translated by Google) Great, I was able to go twice and I was never disappointed  (Original) Super, j'ai pu y aller deux fois et je n'ai jamais été déçu
Terrible. Run by a bunch of unprofessional kids. Server admitted that they drink the byob bottles since they keep any bottles you bring in the kitchen.
I love Schwa. It is a unique, fun experience. Love the food and that it is BYOB.
So imaginative and delicious

Truly an amazing dining experience. The food was superb, service was excellent and the atmosphere is spectacular. I would go here again in a heartbeat! The chef even had us come back to the kitchen to take a shot with us. BTW - bring the staff a bottle of Jameson - they’ll appreciate it!
Food great. Total bum rush.
Amazing experience. Most creative dishes I've ever had. Made my engagement day even more memorable
Mind blowing. Absolutely worth it for sure. Staff was extremely knowledgeable and friendly. No corkage fee. For was on a whole nother level!
Very creative food that tastes great too. Atmosphere is also awesome. This is a place you have to experience for yourself.

Modernist Chicago original.  Cuisine is out of the box creative.  Frequent menu changes.  Unusual aromatics like Japanese white Birch transform your pallette and add dimension to taste.  Beyond all of that, the food is fantastic.
A singular experience. Go.
Amazing flavors and presentation

An awesome minimalistically decorated space in Wicker Park. One of the most unique BYOB, multi-course meals in the city. The staff made me and my fiancee feel right at home as they are the chefs, servers, and busboys/busgirl for the evening. These dishes are creative masterpieces which make it worth every penny. Enjoying and relax to the loud rap music in the background :)  Quail Egg Raviolo is to die for...Remember to bring the chefs some craft beers along with your alcohol; they will really appreciate it. This was quite the experience and hope to go back in the near future.
Favorite restaurant in Chicago.
Food is impeccable. Environment is not what you expect.  But  every dish blows you away!
I give this place two thumbs up. The service was friendly and observant.
Overall not a fan only liked half the dishes and considering the price I'm glad it was byob.
My fave in Chicago. You can even make reservation online now.
Have been blown away twice by this place. It's unlike anyplace I've been to in this city. Highly recommended.
Had a friend come into town and asked me to take him here again. The place has a nice feel to it.

This was a wonderful experience. The food was unmatched. Every course had a purpose and the ingredients were artfully prepared.  The Chefs were friendly and provided helpful knowledge about what we were eating and why. We were the last people in the restaurant and were invited to have a toast with the kitchen. I appreciated the warm invite. This is a place you must try and then try again. Thank you Schwa for a memorable evening.
Amazing food. Great overall experience, and super cool, dedicated staff. What's not to love???

RUN FAR AND FAST.  My fiance was sick the week of our reservation so I called 3 different days to cancel before the reservation day and they wouldn't answer their phones.  Then they still charged my credit card $400 and won't let us come in there to eat so basically I paid them $400 for nothing.

This restaurant is just OK. The food is plated just nicely enough to skim the definition of gastronomy. The service was short, unprofessional, and unpleasant. The atmosphere is akin to walking into a stuffy house. For the $150 plate, I expected better service or at least a finer experience. Unfortunately there are a lot of restaurants in Chicago that get a lot of play without being legitimately worth the spend, here being one of them. The servers quickly set dishes down and we could barely hear the description with the blaring music. Tables were so tightly set up that it made for uncomfortably close quarters. Music was good but too loud. Lighting was wayyy too dark. Food was, by Chicago’s high standards, just alright. It was just plated nicely. I don’t get the hype about this place. If it’s supposed to mimic a pretentious/exclusive NYC hole in the wall fine dining type of thing (if that is a “thing”), it worked. It’s not fun. Oh and one of the servers def took a smoke break in the middle of his shift and absolutely wreaked.

Saw the waiter drinking out of the bottle he served us water out of in the back.. he also offered me to smoke at the end of the night from weed they smoked that billowed through the dining room. Certainly an element we dont pay to be around. Food was great though, not worth the cost due to atmosphere.

Food was excellent, hands down, a must try restaurant. Service was okay. One thing that we didn't like was how loud the music was blasting. The restaurant itself is a very small room and the music was way too loud for such a small place.
One of the best experiences in Chicago
Hands down the best dining experience I have ever had! Customer  service was outstanding. Do yourself a favor and try Schwa Restaurant!
Great flavors, great service, great playlist. Will come back.
Always awesome
Food is amazing. Atmosphere is very relaxed and informal. Chefs are friendly. Vibes are great.
Google says i ate here. I dont remember that. 4 stars

If you’re going to shell out some bucks for a tasting menu, Schwa is a great call.  First of all, the dishes are inventive and incredibly flavorful. We’ve been a couple times and with the exception of a couple dishes, everything has been incredible.  Not only is the food great, but I actually felt satiated following the meal - a rarity for this type of restaurant.  The last time we went for the 9-course meal, they ended up serving 12 courses.  I might have smelled the aroma of cannibis coming from the kitchen, but I wouldn’t know about that.  Btw, it’s BYOB!
The food was tasty, though the portions were small for the price.
A friend worked in the kitchen...place needs to be shut down disgusting!!!!! Someone call the health department
fantastic meal and great experience, especially for a small group

Was here with a big work group. I loved that fact that we could bring our own wine. The service was very good. Many of the courses were very good and very creative, but a couple were just strange and confusing... i just didn’t think that flavors worked well together. Extremes on both sides. It was an interesting experience, but I’m not sure I’ll be back.
Possibly the most amazing tasting menu I've ever had!
Best dining experience in Chicago.
Weird, wild and wonderful.  An experience in dining that I won't soon forget.
I feel cooler by virtue of having eaten here

I've been here twice, each time a fantastic meal was had.  Of note, Chef uses unique fish plated beautifully.  He experiments.  If you get the feeling you're a guinea pig, you're not that far off.  Michael has a way about him that may rub some people the wrong way.  Don’t despair.  And bring your BEST vino.  And a six pack for the crew.
By in far one of the coolest and most unique meals I've ever had in my life.

Finally got to experience Schwa after talking about it for years. The decor and ambiance is pretty cool, one of the most interesting and minimal layouts you will ever see.  Servers were attentive and friendly. They tended to rattle off the dish ingredients very quickly and without a menu it wasn't easy to pick up on each dish's composition. The music was fine, especially if you like hip hop from the 90s. Some of the dishes were quite good - the mackerel stood out and crispy mustard greens with ham broth as well - but many courses had flavors that clashed seemingly just to clash. The bigger issue was the level of salt in at least half of the dishes. I get that higher end places don't skimp on the extra salt, but this was overdone and really distracted from some of the flavors. At that price level it's pretty disappointing.
Love the food it's the best
Really delicious and fun experience!

Schwa serves a variety of inventive dishes and flavors, at The intersection of the familiar and unknown. Every course included something I've had many times over, but all were served with a new spin on flavors that I've never tried combined. And while this is fine dining, at its finest, they have a great byob policy that keeps cost dish and lets you pick wine or beer that you'll enjoy. Do the right thing, and bring some extra for the chefs.
Beyond compare

Absolutely loved everything from the relaxed environment to the amazing staff and of course every part of the meal. Everything was impeccable and I cannot thank them enough for making accommodations for my dietary restrictions due to chemo. Hands down the best dining experience I've had in a very, very long time.
Incredible food, awesome staff & great music

A bizarre, but amazing culinary experience. Our first course wasn't food, but rather a cocktail. You were supposed to smell the provided air fresheners while drinking it. This course kind of sums up the place. It's different. But awesome.
Heard all the stuff, totally blown away.  Food I don't love was still amazing, service was fun and guys were informative but not pretentious.  Great time and we will be back soon!
Cannot think of a better spot. If you have a sense of humor and have an open mind on food, this is the place. Hands off to the chefs, staff and all else involved. The absolute best
We really love this place! We've had their taquitos, tacos, enchilada.. All good! Not to much of a fan of their fajitas (no skillet!), but their salsa is delicious!

Well.....very interesting menu when you are reading it. It creats a huge expectation of something unique and unusual. However  the reality of food is, at best, mediocre. I would definitly not spend another $400 here. Two times are enough, when they are too mediocre for such a high price ticket.
It would be great if they ever actually were open and honored their reservations...

Not positive it's the BEST meal I've ever had, but it was certainly the most fun restaurant I've ever been to.  Truly an experience everyone should have at least once.  I hope to go back sometime very soon!  Terrific place.
Everyone working there seems chill, which is a nice change of pace to other fine dining experiences. The type of creations you get to experience are amazing.
Easily the best meal we had in Chicago. Great music and atmosphere, definitely not pretentious, and everyone seemed friendly and in a good mood.
Fire.
Innovative, approachable, legendary.

Huge flavors in a laid back environment. As a chef I can say, these guys really know world class food. We ate at other Michelin star restaurants on our visit and Schwa took the cake. Lots of playfulness with just enough sense of restraint. Bravo guys, you've really got something special going on there! Make sure to bring booze for yourself and for the kitchen (brown liquor or fernet). Get ready to have your mind blown!
The owner Vinny is one of the nicest guys I've met.

Super interesting menu and good quality but it was kinda tough to keep up. Went from white chocolate to french toast to a greek style dish. It was a fun experience but I am not dying to return. The atmosphere is super cool and love that all the employees are tatted men.
great food and laid back fun staff

This was the best meal of my life! I left so full I thought I would burst, and had to slouch in the cab on the way home to be comfortable. :) It's a fixed menu, 12 courses I believe, but they were trying out new dishes so we had even more than that. It's not an uppity environment, they play rap music in the kitchen. It's byob too which is really great for a restaurant like this. One tip - bring a bottle or some beer for the chefs. I wish we would have known that before we went! I hope we'll go back sometime!

We have been here twice - each time loved the food, the unpretentious atmosphere, and the good-natured, low key service. The dishes were amazing -- thoughtful and inspired twists on the familiar, wonderful flavors, beautifully presented.  I was worried that the second visit would be a disappointment after loving the first visit. We loved it just as much or more the second time.
If you can get a reservation - go.  Anytime, from anywhere.  Truly awesome.
Too good, too much fun, too damn cool not to more recognized!
Bring whiskey!
Rockin BYOB! Good luck getting a reservation, but if you are able to get through you will not be sorry
Unpretentious fine dining. Decor, or lack there of, fits the no frills experience. Nothing to distract from what a restaurant should be about: The food.

This is the best place I've ever eaten. And not just because of the favors of the food, but because of the emotions that each dish conjured up. The staff is scrappy, but so kind and beyond impassioned. I'd kill just to hang out and grab some beers with them on any given night. Food can be exotic without being pretentious and that's what Schwa managed to do. I still dream about the skate wing w/ Kim Chee IPA!

I really wish I could offer a good review, especially after reading past reviews.  However, when they call you on a Saturday afternoon to essentially say they don't feel like opening up that night, they should expect some knocks.  Schwa, be quirky all you want - don't pick up your phone and only open when you feel like it - just don't expect that I'll ever be a customer.
The only problem here is that I can rarely get a table!!
